Package: quickrepo
Version: 2.0.0
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: python3 (>= 3.8), python3-pip, python3-requests, python3-setuptools, git, gh
Maintainer: Daniel Rosehill <daniel@danielrosehill.com>
Bugs: https://github.com/danielrosehill/quick-repo-creator/issues
Description: CLI tool for quickly creating GitHub repositories with optional AI development templates
 QuickRepo is a command-line interface that streamlines the process of creating
 GitHub repositories. It supports dual naming systems (GitHub vs local filesystem),
 optional AI development workspace templates, and integrates with GitHub's API
 for seamless repository creation and cloning.
 .
 Features include:
  - Dual naming system for GitHub readability and filesystem compatibility
  - AI development template with structured workspace directories
  - Interactive prompts for repository configuration
  - Automatic local cloning after repository creation
Homepage: https://github.com/danielrosehill/quick-repo-creator
